  "prompt": "What is the salary of an RTO officer?",
  "response": "The salary of an RTO (Regional Transport Officer) can vary based on factors such as the state or region in which they work, their experience, and the level of government (state, central, etc.). Generally, RTO officers in India can expect a salary range from approximately \u20b930,000 to \u20b960,000 per month, depending on their position and qualifications.\n\nIn addition to the base salary, RTO officers may receive various allowances and benefits, which can include travel allowances, medical benefits, and retirement plans. For the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's best to refer to official government job postings or resources specific to the region in question.",
